<p>I want to have multiple subdomains all showing same content as main domain. For example: a.domain.com, b.domain.com should have same content as domain.com.</p>  <p>For that I used multisite code:</p>  <pre><code>RewriteEngine On RewriteBase / RewriteRule ^index\.php$ - [L]  # add a trailing slash to /wp-admin RewriteRule ^wp-admin$ wp-admin/ [R=301,L]  RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f [OR] RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d RewriteRule ^ - [L] RewriteRule ^(wp-(content|admin|includes).*) $1 [L] RewriteRule ^(.*\.php)$ $1 [L] RewriteRule . index.php [L] </code></pre>  <p>Here, the problem is the subdomain site is also showing the main domain site content. For example: I see <code>&lt;link rel="canonical" href="http://domain.com/" /&gt;</code> instead of <code>&lt;link rel="canonical" href="http://a.domain.com/" /&gt;</code> How to solve the problem?</p>